      • publish

        public int publish​(java.lang.String pSubjectName,
                   byte[] pData)
            throws DistributorException
        Description copied from interface: DistributorPublisherIf
        Publish an update on the connection. When publishing data a subject/topic is associated with the update. Subscribers can when setting up subscriptions specify what subjects/topics they have an interest in. The distributor will perform the filtering and just deliver updates that match the subjects/topics the subscriber has an interest in. The subject string is a Hierarchical name string where levels are divided by the character "/" for example "/foo/bar/fie ". The characters (strings) "* " and "... " works as wildcards. These wildcard strings must not be present in a subject when publishing data but are applicable when setting up an subscription. The "* " match any string at a certain level, for example "/foo/* /fie" will match any string at the second level. The string "... " matches all strings at the current level and all sublevels, for example "/foo/... " will match "/foo/bar/fie " and "/foo/allan/gazonk/47111 " etc.
        Specified by:
        publish in interface DistributorPublisherIf
        Parameters:
        pSubjectName - subject name
        pData - data to be published
        Returns:
        the time in usec the IP transmission took i.e. the time spent in the sendto
        Throws:
        DistributorException
